-- Burundi Tea Output Rose 10% to 8,816 Tons Last Year, Agency Says
-- B y   D e s i r e   N i m u b o n a
-- 2012-01-27T16:00:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/burundi-tea-output-rose-10-to-8-816-tons-last-year-agency-says.html
Production of tea in  Burundi  rose 10
percent last year to 8,816 metric tons, the Burundi Tea
Authority said today.  Turnover reached 29.1 billion Burundi francs ($21 million)
from 23.5 billion francs in 2010, the agency said in a statement
handed to reporters today in Bujumbura, the capital. It earned
$22.2 million from exports of tea, up from $18.2 million a year
earlier, it said.  The average price for a kilogram (2.2 pounds) of the leaves
rose to $2.80 in the year from $2.49 in 2010, the authority
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Desire Nimubona in Bujumbura via Accra at 
